<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="685" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/6438</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-09">September 9, 1929</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                October 28.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1143</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Supplementing my despatch No. 1130 of
                            August 24, 1929, I have the honor to inform the Department that Gabry
                            Rivas and Adan Morales Z. were released from confinement nine days after
                            their arrest on the charge of conspiracy. Investigation of the charge
                            did not produce sufficient evidence to justify a formal accusation
                            against them.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Matthew E. Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>